🎼 Orbit House V1 — Generative Rhythm MIDI System
🧭 Overview
Orbit House V1 is a generative rhythm architecture system that produces MIDI patterns based on phase-based grid cycles and layered percussion logic.
Instead of traditional beat-making, this system uses structured time cycles to generate rhythm through interaction between independent layers.
The result is not a fixed song — but a repeatable rhythm engine that outputs evolving grooves.
🧠 Core Concept
The system is built on the idea that rhythm can be generated using independent step cycles that interact over time.
Orbit House uses three primary cycle lengths:
8-step cycle → Anchor layer (stability)
10-step cycle → Groove layer (movement)
11-step cycle → Drift layer (variation / tension)
These cycles do not align perfectly, creating phase-based polyrhythmic movement.
🥁 Layer Architecture
1. Sub Log (Anchor Layer)
Provides rhythmic foundation
Typically mapped to kick / sub elements
Maintains structural stability
2. Rhythm Log (Groove Layer)
Drives groove movement
Often mapped to log drum / bass percussion
Adds syncopation and flow
3. Accent Log (Texture Layer)
Adds rhythmic variation and detail
High-frequency percussion (hats, clicks, accents)
Creates movement on top of groove
4. Fill Log (Optional Layer)
Used for transitions and variation
Not always active
Introduces rhythmic change events
🔁 System Behaviour
Orbit House V1 operates as a phase interaction system:
Each layer runs independently
No forced alignment between cycles
Groove emerges from time displacement
Repetition evolves through phase drift, not pattern change
